notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56CI.
issue_obverse_legend_s: Two Shillings & Six-pence. THIS Indented BILL shall pass current for Two Shillings & Six pence, according to an Act of General Assembly of the Counties of Newcastle, Kent and Sussex, upon Delaware, passed in the 15th Year of the Reign of His Majes. Geo. the 3d. Dated the First Day of Jan. 1776.
issue_reverse_legend_s: Two Shillings and Six-pence. To Counterfeit is Death. Printed by JAMES ADAMS, 1776.
